                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Fraud Prevention and Location Verification in Credit Scoring</h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm mt-4">
                    <div class="bg-red-50/50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-100">
                        <strong class="text-red-800 font-semibold block mb-1">The Friction (Traditional Way):</strong>
                        When applying for instant micro-loans or BNPL (Buy Now Pay Later) services, risk mitigation algorithms calculate geographical credit scores (as certain areas display higher non-performing loan indexes). Fraudulent users often manipulate inputs, picking low-risk dropdown locations (e.g., Tashkent Center) while residing elsewhere to skew the scoring metric.
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50/50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-100">
                        <strong class="text-green-800 font-semibold block mb-1">The Kettu Solution (Automatic UX):</strong>
                        The microservice automatically grabs the device's true background GPS telemetry and resolves it against Kettu. Kettu responds with the absolute district slug (e.g., <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded font-mono text-xs">"shofirkon"</code>). If Kettu's resolved location conflicts with the user's declared profile fields, the application flags it as a high-risk location anomaly, automatically blocking fraud attempts.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

