                        <strong class="text-red-800 font-semibold block mb-1">The Friction (Traditional Way):</strong>
                        A large retail chain wants to launch an exclusive flash-sale push notification targeting only users currently within a specific neighborhood. Running real-time spatial intersection database operations across millions of roaming user rows crashes standard relational databases, while commercial map APIs charge thousands of dollars for mass geocoding lookups.
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50/50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-100">
                        <strong class="text-green-800 font-semibold block mb-1">The Kettu Solution (Automatic UX):</strong>
                        As background user coordinates occasionally refresh, they hit Kettu's highly cached endpoints to maintain a simple string column: <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">current_district_slug = 'chilanzar'</code>. When marketing fires a campaign, instead of expensive polygon operations, they run a trivial, lightning-fast SQL fetch: <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">WHERE current_district_slug = 'chilanzar'</code>, deploying targeted push messages safely and for free.
                    </div>
                </div>
